<ItacAcademyItem AcademyId="0015" RecordId="021-000000989"><Name>Traccia (Accademia della)</Name><AlternativeName>Accademia fisicomatematica|Accademia dei Filosofi</AlternativeName><City CityId="1"><CityItalianName>Bologna</CityItalianName><CityEnglishName>Bologna</CityEnglishName><CityLatinName>Bononiae</CityLatinName></City><StartDate>1665</StartDate><EndDate>1678/79</EndDate><DateText>1665-1678/79</DateText><Notes>The Academy was first held at Sampieri`s house, and subsequently at Montanari`s house. After Montanari`s departure from Bologna, it was probably hosted by Cardinal Davia for a short time. Details can be found in Salvatore Rotta, `Scienza e pubblica felicit&#224; in Geminiano Montanari`, in Miscellanea Seicento Firenze Le Monnier 1971 pp. 97 and 165-6. This Academy was followed by the Accademia degli Inquieti, see M. Cavazza, `Dal "Coro anatomico" agli "Inquieti", in Quaderni storici (1981). See also Ivano Dal Prete`s biography of Montanari, in DBI.</Notes><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7420" RecordId="022-000000999"><Name>Sampieri, Antonio, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7410" RecordId="022-000001006"><Name>Pasini, Angelo, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7411" RecordId="022-000001008"><Name>Coris, Giovanni Battista, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7413" RecordId="022-000001009"><Name>Pepoli,Taddeo (Paolo Emilio), , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7414" RecordId="022-000001010"><Name>Pinchiari,Agostino Sante, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7416" RecordId="022-000001012"><Name>Zani, Ercole, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7417" RecordId="022-000001013"><Name>Castelli, Prospero Filippo, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7418" RecordId="022-000001014"><Name>Davia, Giovanni Antonio, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="5028" RecordId="022-000000030"><Name>Montanari,Geminiano,,1633 - 1687</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="5151" RecordId="022-000000146"><Name>Manzi,Giovanni Galeazzo,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="5080" RecordId="022-000000077"><Name>Nanni Fantuzzi,Ippolito,,ca. 1609 - 1677</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="18742" RecordId="022-000005809"><Name>Guglielmini,Domenico (Bolognese),,1655 - 1710</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="19412" RecordId="022-000006620"><Name>Rondelli,Geminiano,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><Citation>Lorenza Gianfrancesco and Simone Testa, directed by Jane Everson, Denis Reidy, Lisa Sampson, assisted by Thomas Denman, for the Italian Academies Database project.</Citation></ItacAcademyItem>